A Non-Governmental Organisation (NGO), Friends From Cradle Foundation, has donated Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) to the General Hospital in Badagry, Lagos State. Its President, Dr. Michael Kunnuji, said the donation was made to assist the workers protect themselves against infection. Said he: “We are here today to support Badagry General Hospital in the area of PPE provision, to assist the workers, especially during this COVID-19 pandemic. “We have contributed our widow’s mite in providing these equipment to assist the workers to further reduce the spread of COVID-19.” Kunnuji said the equipment included 120 pieces of face mask, 1,000 pieces of hand glove and five pieces of face shield. He said the foundation made the donation to support Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu’s efforts to tackle the pandemic. The Deputy Medical Director of the hospital, Dr. Olatunde Bakare, said the management was delighted to receive the equipment.